{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_82c204bcd79547928a7a0d8d","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t.. _dev-getting-started:\n2\t\n3\tGetting Started\n4\t***************\n5\t\n6\tRequired knowledge\n7\t==================\n8\t\n9\t  * Python 3\n10\t  * JavaScript (ES5, ES6 or CoffeeScript)\n11\t  * basic AngularJS knowledge (modules & controllers)\n12\t  * basic HTML skills\n13\t\n14\tSetting up development environment\n15\t==================================\n16\t\n17\t1. Install Ajenti\n18\t-----------------\n19\t\n20\tWe recommend to use the automatic installer - see the :ref:`installation guide <installing>`\n21\t\n22\t2. Install build tools\n23\t----------------------\n24\t\n25\tBuild tools require NodeJS - you can use the NodeSource repositories for quick setup::\n26\t\n27\t    # Using Ubuntu\n28\t    curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_18.x | sudo -E bash -\n29\t    sudo apt-get install -y nodejs\n30\t\n31\t    # Using Debian, as root\n32\t    curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_18.x | bash -\n33\t    apt-get install -y nodejs\n34\t\n35\t    # Using RHEL, as root\n36\t    curl -sL https://rpm.nodesource.com/setup_18.x | bash -\n37\t\n38\tNow, install the build tools::\n39\t\n40\t    npm -g install bower babel-cli babel-preset-es2015 babel-plugin-external-helpers less coffee-script angular-gettext-cli angular-gettext-tools\n41\t\n42\t    # Ubuntu or Debian:\n43\t    apt-get install gettext\n44\t\n45\t    # RHEL\n46\t    dnf install gettext\n47\t\n48\t\n49\t3. Install ajenti-dev-multitool\n50\t-------------------------------\n51\t\n52\t    pip3 install ajenti-dev-multitool\n53\t\n54\tYour first plugin\n55\t=================\n56\t\n57\t    Create a new plugin in the current directory::\n58\t\n59\t        ajenti-dev-multitool --new-plugin \"Some plugin name\"\n60\t\n61\t    Build resources::\n62\t\n63\t        cd some_plugin_name\n64\t        ajenti-dev-multitool --build\n65\t\n66\t    And start it::\n67\t\n68\t        sudo ajenti-dev-multitool --run-dev\n69\t\n70\t    This will start Ajenti with the stock plugins plus the current one, and will rebuild plugin resources every time you reload Ajenti in browser.\n71\t\n72\t    Navigate to http://localhost:8000/. You should see new plugin in the sidebar.\n73\t\n74\t\n75\tWhat's inside\n76\t=============\n77\t\n78\tEach plugin package consists of Python modules, which contain :class:`jadi.component` classes (*components*).\n79\tPackages also may contain :ref:`static files, templates and JS and CSS code <dev-resources>`, e.g.::\n80\t\n81\t      * some_plugin_name\n82\t        - plugin.yml # plugin description\n83\t        - __init__.py\n84\t        - other_python_module.py\n85\t        * resources\n86\t          * vendor\n87\t            - jquery-ui # Bower components\n88\t        * js\n89\t          - module.js # Angular.js code\n90\t          - ecmascript6-code.es\n91\t          - coffeescript-code.coffee\n92\t        * css\n93\t          - styles.css\n94\t          - styles.less\n95\t        * partials\n96\t          -- index.html\n97\t\n98\t\n99\tWhere to go from here\n100\t=====================\n101\t\n102\tExample plugins\n103\t---------------\n104\t\n105\t    Download plugins from here: https://github.com/ajenti/demo-plugins or clone this entire repository.\n106\t\n107\t    Prep work::\n108\t\n109\t        ajenti-dev-multitool --bower install\n110\t        ajenti-dev-multitool --rebuild\n111\t\n112\t    Run::\n113\t\n114\t        ajenti-dev-multitool --run-dev\n115\t\n116\t    .. HINT::\n117\t      Changes in ES6, CoffeeScript and LESS files will be recompiled automatically when you refresh the page; Python code will not. Additional debug information will be available in the console output and browser console. Reloading the page with Ctrl-F5 (``Cache-Control: no-cache``) will unconditionally rebuild all resources\n118\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f881cebb-6592-4c40-a00f-2bdf7c835e8c","uuid":"12a363cc-c707-4944-a0b9-be2bfcdd8430","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:09:24.703Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/source/dev/intro.rst","content":".. _dev-getting-started:\n\nGetting Started\n***************\n\nRequired knowledge\n==================\n\n  * Python 3\n  * JavaScript (ES5, ES6 or CoffeeScript)\n  * basic AngularJS knowledge (modules & controllers)\n  * basic HTML skills\n\nSetting up development environment\n==================================\n\n1. Install Ajenti\n-----------------\n\nWe recommend to use the automatic installer - see the :ref:`installation guide <installing>`\n\n2. Install build tools\n----------------------\n\nBuild tools require NodeJS - you can use the NodeSource repositories for quick setup::\n\n    # Using Ubuntu\n    curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_18.x | sudo -E bash -\n    sudo apt-get install -y nodejs\n\n    # Using Debian, as root\n    curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_18.x | bash -\n    apt-get install -y nodejs\n\n    # Using RHEL, as root\n    curl -sL https://rpm.nodesource.com/setup_18.x | bash -\n\nNow, install the build tools::\n\n    npm -g install bower babel-cli babel-preset-es2015 babel-plugin-external-helpers less coffee-script angular-gettext-cli angular-gettext-tools\n\n    # Ubuntu or Debian:\n    apt-get install gettext\n\n    # RHEL\n    dnf install gettext\n\n\n3. Install ajenti-dev-multitool\n-------------------------------\n\n    pip3 install ajenti-dev-multitool\n\nYour first plugin\n=================\n\n    Create a new plugin in the current directory::\n\n        ajenti-dev-multitool --new-plugin \"Some plugin name\"\n\n    Build resources::\n\n        cd some_plugin_name\n        ajenti-dev-multitool --build\n\n    And start it::\n\n        sudo ajenti-dev-multitool --run-dev\n\n    This will start Ajenti with the stock plugins plus the current one, and will rebuild plugin resources every time you reload Ajenti in browser.\n\n    Navigate to http://localhost:8000/. You should see new plugin in the sidebar.\n\n\nWhat's inside\n=============\n\nEach plugin package consists of Python modules, which contain :class:`jadi.component` classes (*components*).\nPackages also may contain :ref:`static files, templates and JS and CSS code <dev-resources>`, e.g.::\n\n      * some_plugin_name\n        - plugin.yml # plugin description\n        - __init__.py\n        - other_python_module.py\n        * resources\n          * vendor\n            - jquery-ui # Bower components\n        * js\n          - module.js # Angular.js code\n          - ecmascript6-code.es\n          - coffeescript-code.coffee\n        * css\n          - styles.css\n          - styles.less\n        * partials\n          -- index.html\n\n\nWhere to go from here\n=====================\n\nExample plugins\n---------------\n\n    Download plugins from here: https://github.com/ajenti/demo-plugins or clone this entire repository.\n\n    Prep work::\n\n        ajenti-dev-multitool --bower install\n        ajenti-dev-multitool --rebuild\n\n    Run::\n\n        ajenti-dev-multitool --run-dev\n\n    .. HINT::\n      Changes in ES6, CoffeeScript and LESS files will be recompiled automatically when you refresh the page; Python code will not. Additional debug information will be available in the console output and browser console. Reloading the page with Ctrl-F5 (``Cache-Control: no-cache``) will unconditionally rebuild all resources\n","numLines":118,"startLine":1,"totalLines":118}}}
